The paper deals with training deep neural networks for visual object recognition and detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a generic way to handle noisy and incomplete labeling, which is a common problem in many machine learning applications, and thus could be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
